<TITLE> Man found dead on Airport Road was NSU teacher </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 26 (bdnews24.com)  A man who was found dead on the Airport Road Tuesday night has been identified as Dewan Rahat Karim Mukul, teacher of North South University, police said Wednesday. The police immediately failed to unpack the circumstances surrounding the death of the lecturer of the School of Business at NSU. "Relatives identified the body," Gulshan police sub-inspector Mainul Zakir told bdnews24.com. Mukul, son of Dewan Abdul Matin, an engineer for the Roads and Highways Department, was taken to Dhaka Medical College Hospital for an autopsy. Quoting Mukul's family, Zakir said the 32-year-old teacher left his Dhanmondi home at about 8:30am Tuesday for the universitynever to return alive. Zakir said the police would investigate the death in unclear circumstances. Mukul's family did not name any suspect. "We have to see if muggers killed him or a personal enmity was at the heart of the death," he said. Mukul's elder brother Tutul studies in Canada. The family's ancestral home is in Chandpur. bd
